[{"id":"VR718663","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block on a horizontal surface attached to one end of a horizontal spring, and the other end of the spring is attached to a wall.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR718663.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block on a horizontal surface is attached to one end of a spring, and the other end of the spring is attached to a fixed wall, as shown in the figure. The block is released from rest at a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub 0\"><math alttext=\"d sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> to the right of its equilibrium position and oscillates with negligible friction along the horizontal surface. The block has a speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub max\"><math alttext=\"v sub max\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>max</mi></msub></math></span></span> when it passes through the equilibrium position. What is the instantaneous speed of the block when it is at a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction d sub 0, end sub, over 2, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction d sub 0, end sub, over 2, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><msub><mi>d</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> from equilibrium?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR718663_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one fourth, v sub max\"><math alttext=\"one fourth, v sub max\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>max</mi></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half, v sub max\"><math alttext=\"one half, v sub max\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>max</mi></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 1, and denominator the square root of 2, end fraction, v sub max\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 1, and denominator the square root of 2, end fraction, v sub max\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>max</mi></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator the square root of 3, end root, and denominator 2, end fraction, v sub max\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator the square root of 3, end root, and denominator 2, end fraction, v sub max\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>max</mi></msub></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]